      "## Problem 1.11\n",
      "\n",
      "A number, a, is a power of b if it is divisible by b and a/b is a power of b. Write a function called `is_power` that takes parameters a and b and returns True if a is a power of b. Note: you will have to think about the base case."
     ]
    },
    {
     "cell_type": "code",
     "collapsed": false,
     "input": [
      "# Problem 1.11\n",
      "\n",
      "# if a = power of b\n",
      "\n",
      "def is_power(a,b):\n",
      "\n",
      "    if a == 0 or b == 0 or b == 1 or a < b:\n",
      "        return False\n",
      "    elif a % b == 0:\n",
      "        if (a/b)/b == 1:\n",
      "            return True\n",
      "        else:\n",
      "            return is_power(a/b,b)\n",
      "    else:\n",
      "        return False\n",
      "\n",
      "print is_power(1,2)\n",
      "print is_power(4,2)\n",
      "print is_power(2,1)"
     ],
     "language": "python",
     "metadata": {},
     "outputs": [
      {
       "output_type": "stream",
       "stream": "stdout",
       "text": [
        "False\n",
        "True\n",
        "False\n"
       ]
      }
     ],
